cs.IR, cs.CL, cs.SI, cs.SD, cs.CY 

This paper is likely to belong to the Information Retrieval (cs.IR) sub-category as it discusses the use of link information to improve ranking and crawling algorithms in Web search. It also touches upon natural language processing (cs.CL) by formalizing the clink-content conjecture, which infers the lexical content of a page based on the pages that link to it. The paper also discusses the semantic meaning of pages and how they are clustered together, which could fall under the sub-categories of Social and Information Networks (cs.SI) and Sound and Music Computing (cs.SD). Finally, the paper's focus on the structure and topology of the Web could also place it in the sub-category of Computers and Society (cs.CY).
